<a href="javascript:card_browser(104)">Blade Tip</a> (x3)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(953)">Wizard Storm</a> (x4)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Truly this deck is amazing against big minions that cost lots of twilight pool, but it suffers against swarms and other decks with lots of little minions. The key is always Merry and sometimes Boromir. For example, if your Aragorn faces and ugly Lurtz, Merry and Boromir together could give him a bonus strenght of +6, +9, even +11... it&#39;s great, no? The problem comes when Merry is forced to be assigned, but Boromir can help in this case. <br>
Saruman snows can &quot;freeze&quot; your Merry and Boromir, so that&#39;s why I&#39;ve thought about Boromir&#39;s cloak. <br>
The shadow part is very easy to play and to understand. Everybody knows that one of the worst problems for Nazgûl is the flaming brand, so that&#39;s why there are 4 isengard smith and 2 trapped and alone. Isengard warrior may be helpul against archery companions, and combinated with the Witch-King can play a good part. Moreover, if your opponent can&#39;t beat your Nazgûl, will be &quot;convinced&quot; to stop, and if you play wizard storm and play your black breath and blade tip on his/her companions, he will die soon if moving twice. <br>
Of course, this deck is funny to play, but, in my opinion, looks weak against some hazard decks. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=25954"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25954" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
